        },
        "text": "The Arabic word for 'doctor' is 'طبيب' (ṭabīb) for a male and 'طبيبة' (ṭabībah) for a female. Notice the addition of the feminine 'ة' (tāʾ marbūṭah) at the end for the female form.",
